<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1111">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Italy)/7–1745:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>No. 1111<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi>
                                        (<persName corresp="#p_KA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">plain</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-17">July 17, 1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>2010. Most Rome papers this morning carry United Press item
                                    stating that <persName corresp="#p_DCJHJ1">Colonel James
                                        Henderson Douglas</persName> will arrive in Italy probably
                                    on July 24 to assume post of Chief Commissioner of Allied
                                    Commission replacing Admiral <persName corresp="#p_SRAEW1">Stone</persName> (see my 1877, July 7th<note n="1" xml:id="d1111fn1">Not printed.</note>).</p>
                                <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_KA1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>